text: - I'm Wendy, I'm an AWS data hero.

I'm from Sydney, and I'm
really passionate about data.
I'm fascinated by generative AI.

And so when AWS released
Amazon Code Whisperer

in April this year, I
jumped on the bandwagon

and I thought, I'm going
to learn on Skill Builder
all about Amazon Code Whisperer,

how to apply that
knowledge, the use cases,
and how to install AWS Toolkit.
The learning through AWS Skill Builder

has actually helped me
to consolidate knowledge
as a data scientist,

and also undertake self-paced
learning in my own Time.

Builder's Labs helped me
to build the confidence

that I needed and the experience
to apply my knowledge,

to build architectural
solutions, to design.

The exam prep and the
exam practice questions

were crucial in my learning
journey to enable me

to pass the AWS Solution Architect
Associate the first time.

And it really helped me
to build solid foundations

in IT computing and cloud
skills and apply that at work,

and also to help me to write
more technical blogs as well
to teach my learners.
(bright music)
